ntsb3110txt-1-5-5-0-6 The aircraft flight manual (AFM) prohibited flight in icing conditions above 26,000 feet (except when necessary for descent). 
ntsb3110txt-1-5-5-0-7 Also, the AFM stipulated the minimum engine speeds which needed to be maintained while operating in icing conditions; it also required that the thrust management system (TMS) be disconnected in icing conditions. 
ntsb3110txt-1-5-5-0-8 There were indications that the TMS was disconnected about 230 seconds after engine roll-back began. 
